FT  16 OCT 93 / Madrid calls car crisis talks
The Spanish government yesterday called emergency talks with carmakers to
seek solutions to the crisis in the sector, Reuter reports from Madrid.
The Industry Ministry also said officials would leave today for a visit to
Japan, where they will discuss the problem with chairmen of leading motor
companies.
Industry Minister Juan Manuel Eguiagaray is expected to ask Nissan and
Suzuki to maintain their presence in Spain, despite heavy losses. Nissan has
already halted two capital increases of Pta10bn (Pounds 50.5m)
'We have had no official communication suggesting any plan to pull out of
Spain, but rumours are rife and we will be seeking clarification,' said the
ministry.
